	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jun 27th 1:48 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1090 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, my turn to answer this one.&nbsp;&nbsp;Daviv check my work please....<br><br>Dual Wield is a combat skill rogues (and warriors, monks and bards) recieve at some point in their careers.  It allows you to place a 1 handed weapon in each hand and then gives you a chance to attack with both weapons.  The higher your skill in DW the more likely you will get a chance at attacking with your secondary hand weapon.<br><br>First, you need to understand how weapon delay works.  Every weapon has a delay rating. The lower the delay the faster it will make an attack attempt.  You can take the delay rating divided by 10 and that will give the number of seconds, approximately, between attack attempts.  Each attack attempt can miss or hit for varying damage (thats another long story). <br><br>The weapon in your primary melee slot will always make an attack attempt  when the time comes (unless you are stunned or paralyzed) based on its delay rating. Success is determined by your skill with that weapon type. The weapon in your secondary melee slot will, when it's time comes to attack (based on its delay rating), first check against your Dual Wield skill to see if the attack attempt will take place.  Then, if the DW check succeeds, an attack attempt is made based on your weapon skill for that weapon type.<br><br>As you get better with DW you will more frequently see attacks from each weapon.  Combined with Double Attack you could see up to 2 attacks from each weapon for a total of 4 attacks, seemingly at the same time. <br><br>At level 13 you have a long way to go before you see an attack from each weapon on a frequent basis but hang in there.  The skill will go up on its own without special training (just put at least one training point into the skill at the rogue trainer).  Keep a weapon in each melee slot at all times.  A high DEX score will help the skill go up faster.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
