	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jun 27th 5:15 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=73658><span id=Sage>DavivMcD</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>300 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Very, very good job on this one guys:) A couple of other points: Rangers get dual wield too.<br><br>The dual wield skill has a higher cap than most other general and combat skills. For most skills, you can only get a skill up to (your level +1) * 5, except for offense and defense, which are just (your level) * 5. And of course trade skills, which have a cap of 250 for your first one above 200 and 200 for the others...Anyway, dual wield will let you go up to (your level +1) * 6, which you may or may not notice. DEX is one way to help improve your skill more, another way is to put a lower delay weapon in your offhand. Since it only does a improve skill check every time your offhand weapon delay passes, a low delay weapon will give you more chances to improve in the skill. Early on just put any crappy weapon in your offhand that has a low delay; since you won't be hitting much with it anyway you don't need high damage. Later on in the game you will find that most better ratio weapons will have low delays anyway.<br><br>As soon as you get double attack (level 16), only your main hand will have a chance to double attack, therefore you will start seeing triple attacks, but not four attacks yet. As soon as you get your double attack skill at least 150 (level 29 at earliest), your offhand will do checks for double attack as well, and you can start getting quadruple hits.<br><br>This doesn't exactly fit the post, but something interesting I found is that you don't need to hit with a proccing weapon for the proc to hit. In the case of an offhand weapon you just need succeed the dual wield check. The proc check is separate from hitting.</p>&nbsp;<br>Daviv McD (Un-retired!)<br>36th Dwarf Rogue<br>Fury Fighters<br>Xegony<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=13233</a></td></td></tr>
